description: September 14, 2020: With Bulletin N. 262, the Italian Ministry of Health announced that the Italian Minister of Health, Roberto Speranza, has attended the 70th session of the WHO Regional Committee for Europe (RC70), organised by the WHO Regional Office for Europe, on September 14 and 15, 2020. Representatives of 53 countries in the WHO European Region have attended. Representatives of WHO partners such as United Nations agencies and other intergovernmental organisations and regional networks, were also present. Non-State actors (NSAs) in official relations with WHO and regional NSAs accredited by the Regional Committee, have followed the webstream and had the opportunity to submit video and written statements in advance. The key health issues and future plans have been discussed, particularly on themes regarding the response to the COVID-19 pandemic and lessons learned from the pandemic, both globally and regionally.

Further exceptions to be decided by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and European Integration).  In the most recent update to the border restrictions (July 24), only Moldovan citizens may continue to enter Moldova freely, with exceptions for foreign citizens who are: relatives of Moldovan citizens, non-citizen residents and long-term visa holders, business travellers (with appropriate visas), diplomatic staff or staff of international organizations or missions and their family members, transiting passengers, persons travelling for health or humanitarian reasons (with appropriate documents), cross-border workers, and operators and crew of commercial vehicles. UPDATE: Access to Moldovan territory remains restricted to Moldovan citizens with an expanded list of valid reasons foreign persons may enter Moldova. description: Authorities in Moldova are maintaining international entry restrictions as of Dec. 7 to combat the spread of coronavirus disease (COVID-19). Authorities designate all countries with COVID-19 infection rates of over 100 per 100,000 population as "red" or high-risk locations. Most travelers from red locations are prohibited from entering Moldova, excluding Moldovan citizens and residents and their immediate family members, individuals with a work or study permit for Moldova, individuals in transit, and individuals traveling for urgent reasons. All permitted arrivals from red countries must self-isolate for 14 days upon arrival. As of Dec. 7, 63 countries are designated as red locations, including Canada, France, Germany, Romania, Russia, Spain, Ukraine, the UK, and the US; the full list can be found on the Ministry of Health website.
